sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuthProxy as OAuth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Backend as Dashboard Backend<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus/Thanos<br/>9092/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+

    %% Flow 1: User Dashboard Access
    Note over User,Backend: Flow 1: User Dashboard Access
    User->>Router: HTTPS Request<br/>Port: 443/TCP
    Router->>OAuthProxy: Forward Request<br/>Port: 8443/TCP<br/>TLS 1.2+
    OAuthProxy->>OAuthServer: OAuth Authentication Flow<br/>Port: 6443/TCP<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    OAuthServer-->>OAuthProxy: OAuth Token
    OAuthProxy->>Backend: Proxied Request<br/>Port: 8080/TCP<br/>HTTP + Bearer Token
    Backend-->>OAuthProxy: Response
    OAuthProxy-->>Router: HTTPS Response<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Router-->>User: Dashboard UI

    %% Flow 2: Dashboard API to Kubernetes
    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 2: Dashboard API to Kubernetes
    User->>Backend: API Request via OAuth Proxy<br/>/api/notebooks<br/>Bearer Token
    Backend->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Notebook CR<br/>Port: 6443/TCP<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Backend: API Response
    Backend-->>User: JSON Response via Proxy

    %% Flow 3: Metrics Collection
    Note over Prometheus,Backend: Flow 3: Metrics Collection
    Prometheus->>OAuthProxy: Scrape /metrics<br/>Port: 8443/TCP<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>No Auth (skip-auth-regex)
    OAuthProxy->>Backend: Forward /metrics request<br/>Port: 8080/TCP
    Backend-->>OAuthProxy: Prometheus Metrics
    OAuthProxy-->>Prometheus: Metrics Response

    %% Flow 4: Dashboard queries Prometheus
    Note over Backend,Prometheus: Flow 4: Dashboard Queries Metrics
    Backend->>Prometheus: Query Model Metrics<br/>Port: 9092/TCP<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Prometheus-->>Backend: Metrics Data

    %% Flow 5: WebSocket Communication
    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 5: WebSocket Real-time Updates
    User->>Backend: WebSocket Upgrade<br/>via OAuth Proxy<br/>TLS 1.2+ (upgraded)<br/>Bearer Token
    Backend->>K8sAPI: Watch Kubernetes Resources<br/>Port: 6443/TCP<br/>WebSocket/HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Backend: Resource Events
    Backend-->>User: Live Updates via WebSocket
